  "text": "2-5 CD36 has binding sites for thrombospondin, collagen, long fatty acid apoptotic neutrophils, or oxidised LDL. Pearce et al [CITATION_1] reported that CD36 without the transmembrane region was secreted and bound thrombospondin. Therefore, to clarify the condition of CD36 deficient subjects, not only the types of genomic mutation but also the presence of splicing abnormalities should be examined.",
